  "boundary_status": {
    "fixtures_directory_relative_path": "test/oracles/fixtures/",
    "writable_workspace": true,
    "source_only_metadata": true,
    "no_proprietary_bytes_embedded": true,
    "fixture_owners_directory_relative_path": "test/oracles/",
    "owning_phase": "Phase 02 Reference / Oracle Capture Foundation",
    "notes": "test/oracles/fixtures/ is a writable workspace under the inventory lane scope. Every fixture is a JSON contract artifact under schemaVersion=1 that documents either a pending live reference-binary capture surface (28 of 31) or a settled static-contract snapshot of current visible implementation/reference launch state (3 of 31: capture-implementation-clean-launch-expectations.json, capture-reference-clean-launch.json, capture-startup-sequence.json). The fixtures reference the local DOS executable doom/DOOMD.EXE, the local Windows executable doom/DOOM.EXE, and the local IWAD doom/DOOM1.WAD as authority but never embed those proprietary bytes; only paths, role descriptors, and SHA-256 fingerprints of permitted artifacts are recorded. The inventory does not duplicate the fixtures' own content; it records each fixture's external metadata (filename, embedded stepId or stepIdentifier, embedded stepTitle, optional oracleId or oracleIdentifier, schemaVersion, on-disk size, line count, SHA-256 fingerprint, derived is_pending boolean, derived pending classification arrays) so that future regeneration steps can verify a fixture has actually been replaced with live evidence."
  },
  "implications": [
    "28 of 31 fixtures under test/oracles/fixtures/ are pending live reference-binary capture, replay surface, or implementation surface. Replacing every pending fixture with live evidence is owned by plan_vanilla_parity/steps/02-034-replace-pending-oracle-fixtures-with-live-evidence.md, and the gate that closes Phase 02 without deferred-status fixtures remaining is plan_vanilla_parity/steps/02-035-gate-oracle-foundation-without-deferred-status.md. Any future implementation that introduces a runnable reference-binary capture surface (Phase 02 oracle-capture steps 02-005 capture-doomd-clean-launch-feasibility, 02-006 capture-doom-exe-clean-launch-feasibility, 02-016 capture-startup-sequence-oracle, 02-017..02-033 oracle captures) must update the corresponding pending fixtures and rerun this inventory's focused test to confirm the SHA-256 fingerprints have advanced past the pending baseline.",
    "Fixture stepId/stepIdentifier values reference the prior plan_fps Phase 02 numbering and do not map cleanly to plan_vanilla_parity's 35 Phase 02 step files. Cross-mapping requires reading the fixture's stepTitle (which encodes the conceptual capture, e.g. capture-demo1-playback-checkpoints) and matching it against the current plan_vanilla_parity step title (e.g. plan_vanilla_parity step 02-028 capture-demo-one-playback-oracle). Future fixture-author steps in plan_vanilla_parity should reuse the existing fixture filenames and replace contents in place, not invent new fixture filenames, to preserve cross-test reference paths.",
    "Three fixtures use the older stepIdentifier and oracleIdentifier field names (capture-scripted-combat-path.json, capture-scripted-door-use-path.json, capture-scripted-movement-path.json) while 28 use the newer stepId field name. Eight fixtures expose an OR-FPS-* oracleId and 23 do not. Future Phase 02 fixture authors should standardize on stepId and oracleId for new artifacts, but the existing schema-version-1 contract is locked to the inherited dual-field naming that test consumers (test/oracles/capture-*.test.ts) currently expect.",
    "The closed-enum set of pending evidence signals (top-level-pending-key, status-field-pending-value, hash-status-pending-value, null-live-hash-field, string-token-contains-pending) and the 18 distinct kebab-case pending status codes (contract-only, contract-only-not-executed-by-this-step, pending-clean-launch-music-event-hash, pending-e1m1-start-music-event-hash, pending-implementation, pending-live-capture, pending-live-framebuffer-capture, pending-live-reference-capture, pending-live-reference-run, pending-menu-navigation-music-event-hash, pending-reference-capture, pending-reference-capture-surface, pending-reference-execution, pending-reference-oracle-replay-capture-surface, pending-sfx-audio-hash, pending-unimplemented-side-by-side-surface, pending-unimplemented-surface, static-contract-pending-live-reference-capture) form the canonical vocabulary that downstream Phase 02 capture steps must drain to zero before 02-035 gate-oracle-foundation-without-deferred-status can pass. Any step that introduces a new pending status code without updating this inventory will fail this inventory's focused test.",
    "Fixtures expose 5 distinct top-level pending or deferred keys (deferredLiveHashes, pendingCaptureReason, pendingLiveCapture, pendingLiveHashes, pendingReferenceArtifacts) that mark explicit live-evidence gaps. Reshaping any of these top-level keys is a breaking change for the per-fixture test files under test/oracles/capture-*.test.ts that read the keys to assert pending-state structural invariants; the rename or removal must coordinate with those tests and with this inventory's focused test.",
    "The three non-pending fixtures (capture-implementation-clean-launch-expectations.json step 02-001, capture-reference-clean-launch.json step 02-002, capture-startup-sequence.json step 02-003) are static contracts that pin SHA-256 fingerprints of package.json, src/main.ts, and tsconfig.json (the visible 01-015 launch surface inherited from plan_fps); changes to those source files will break the static-contract fixtures and force a regeneration even though the fixtures are not pending. The inventory's focused test must not regenerate those fingerprints automatically because that would silently mask launch-surface drift; the regeneration is owned by the relevant Phase 02 oracle-capture steps.",
    "test/oracles/fixtures/ is the single shared writable workspace under test/oracles/ that the inventory lane owns for this step; any future fixture introduced under that directory must respect the no-proprietary-bytes rule (only paths, role descriptors, SHA-256 fingerprints), schemaVersion=1, and one of the canonical pending classification signals if it is not yet backed by live evidence. The strict no-proprietary-bytes boundary is shared with the rest of the inventory lane and is anchored by reference/policy.ts (the asset license boundary) and reference/manifests/file-hashes.json (the universal-doom reference bundle hash manifest)."
  ],
